										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A prison is extremely dangerous because it contains the most bizarre elements of society. People have always feared and avoided this place. However, Prison Guard Simulator brings a completely new perspective. It is a simulation game in which the main character is a prison guard. He will have to manage everything that has happened and is happening in this giant prison. Of course, when the player reaches a certain level, he will be promoted. You will need to face more dangerous and difficult-to-manage criminals.</p>
<h3>STRATEGIC MANAGEMENT</h3>
<p>Players will need to manage a lot of things and have proper tactics. They have a very unconscious lifestyle and easily provoke each other. But players will have to make them listen. You will have to be the one who wakes up the earliest and goes to bed the latest. And you also have to be the most responsible person. Your vigilance system must never be lowered, because just 1 minute of negligence can cause the prisoners to rebel.</p>
<ul>
<li><em><strong>Control operations: </strong>All tasks fall on your head. Everything is extremely difficult, causing the player to spend a lot of time in the day to work. You must regulate the pace of the prison and understand the intensity of the prisoners&#8217; activities.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>Manage behavior:</strong> Once you understand the prisoners, you can control them. Each person&#8217;s behavior is different. The obedient ones are easy, but the stubborn ones are the real problem.</em></li>
</ul>
<h3>HIGH-INTENSITY ENVIRONMENT</h3>
<p>Rebellion among prisoners is just a small matter. If they escape from prison, it will be a big deal. These dangerous criminals will definitely cause a lot of harm to society when they escape. When they escape, you will definitely not be the one to catch them. You will have to bear a lot of responsibility for your own negligence. However, if you do not encounter any problems during your work, you will be promoted. Living a luxurious life with this salary is also possible.</p>
<ul>
<li><em><strong>Unique personalities: </strong>Because each person is difficult to control, the player will have to spend a lot of time and effort. When confronting brave people, you will also have to have much stronger measures.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>Constant surveillance:</strong> But do not rely too much on the performance of a few people. They may put on a play for you to see and wait for an opportunity to fight back. Therefore, you must constantly monitor them to avoid unexpected situations.</em></li>
</ul>
